question:
The probability density function of a random variable $x$ is given by:
$$
f(x)=
\begin{cases}
 \dfrac{x^2}{81}, & -3 &lt; x &lt; 6 \\[6pt]
 0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

The joint probability density of $X$ and $Y$ is given as 
$$
f(x,y) = 
\begin{cases}
  \dfrac{x+2y}{3}, & 0 \lt x \lt 1, \; 0 \lt y \lt 1 \\[6pt]
  0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
What is the value of $P\big(Y \leq \tfrac{1}{2} \mid X=\tfrac{1}{2}\big)$?
